The paper focuses on video-based person re-identification, which is a computer vision task related to object recognition and tracking. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an end-to-end approach that involves deep learning and metric learning, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions temporal pooling, which is a technique used in multimedia analysis and retrieval, falling under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two public datasets, which is related to benchmarking and evaluation, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
